333;mso-line-height-rule:exactly;"><div style="margin:0 0 20px;white-space:normal;"><p>{{default contact.first_name "Hi there"}},</p><p>Recently I’ve sent you a handful of emails. The gap most homeowners never hear about. The family in Cape Coral after Ian. The idea that the window itself was never the protection. The Tampa family and the $28,000 they didn’t see coming. And then an invitation you didn’t take.</p><p>I want to be straight with you about that last part. Not booking is not the same as not interested. Letting someone into your home is a real decision, and you’re right to want to know what you’d be walking into before you say yes.</p><p>So let me show you the smaller step that comes first. It’s a 15-minute phone call. We call it a Protection Profile Review.</p><p>No one comes to your house. You get on the phone with a Reece specialist, and together you walk through where your home actually stands today. What’s documented. What’s exposed. Which openings would hold up under review, and which ones quietly wouldn’t. At the end you have your Protection Profile: a clear read on your protection gaps, your documentation gaps, and your honest next step.</p><p>That’s the whole call. No pitch. No pressure. If something on the call points to a reason worth looking at in person, we’ll talk about that then. If it doesn’t, you still keep the read.</p><p>Protection is not what you install. It’s what you can prove. The call is simply where you find out where you stand.</p><p>If you have a question about what we’d cover, just reply. I read every one, and {{custom_values.rep_name}} on my team, your point of contact here, will get back to you. Next, I’ll show you the four-piece system itself, working on one family’s home.</p></div><p style="margin:4px 0 8px;">When you’re ready, you can <a class="lnk" href="{{trigger_link.2WyI3ZTkOTl7VkS4TMaK}}">grab a 15-minute slot</a>. Phone only, no pressure.</p><p style="margin:18px 0 4px 0;color:#122739;">Talk soon,</p><p style="margin: